  "description": "<p>The History oracle contextualizes the object more broadly in your setting and provides a prompt for further defining its backstory. This oracle relates the item either to one of the 14 Truths (pg. 82), to other setting aspects which have respective oracles (e.g., Factions, pg. 348), to aspects of gameplay covered by movesets (E.g., Connections, pg. 162), or to other aspects of your character. Use this table sparingly when you want an object to play a larger role in your story. Also, use the prompt as a chance to revisit your Truths or flesh out the details of your world. I highly recommend building your own History oracles, and possibly even rolling on a Campaign Elements oracle (pg. 385) to closely tie items to your story. An alternative to the History oracle is the Action + Theme Oracles (pg. 296-297).</p>",
